<br>
1)  What makes a magician a magician?<br>
<br>
Answer:  A magician is a summoner.  Like a Wizard is a Damage Dealer, a Necromancer is a DoTer, an Enchanter is a buffer.  All these classes do what they do well.<br>
<br>
2)  But I don't LIKE summoning things on raids!<br>
<br>
Answer:  Then why play a summoner?  Mages from the beginning have been summoners.    I made a mage so I could SUMMON things, not because i wanted to be the uberest damage dealer.<br>
<br>
3)  I don't like being a modrod bish!<br>
<br>
Answer:  As compared to what?  If your goal was to be a damage dealer on a high end raid, I'm sorry, but ya picked the wrong class.  If ya wanna deal damage, play a rogue or warrior or ranger or somethin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
4)  But when I started my mage, we were UBER damage dealers!<br>
<br>
Answer:  And we still are.  Im sure when you were level 20, ya didnt expect to be able to be a damage dealer against a mob 15 levels higher than you, why expect it now?<br>
<br>
Now, Im not saying mages as a class DONT have some issues.  We do.  Our pets shouldnt be USELESS on high end raids, they should be able to be useful to us to a degree.  <br>
<br>
But of course, look at the other support classes:<br>
<br>
Clerics:  Heal.  Heal heal heal buff heal heal med med med heal buff heal.<br>
<br>
Shaman:  Buff buff cannibalize buff heal heal buff slow<br>
<br>
Enchanter:  Buff Buff Buff Buff Med Buff Buff Buff<br>
<br>
Druid:  Buff buff heal buff med buff buff<br>
<br>
And thats just a few of em.<br>
<br>
Now, those classes are the same in a normal group.  <br>
<br>
Now, look at mages:<br>
<br>
High end raid mage:  Trod ad infinitum, with some summons tossed in between<br>
<br>
EXPing mage:  A few summons, AND big damage.<br>
<br>
Out of the other classes that are considered support classes, Shaman are the only ones that can really do like we can NOT on raids.<br>
<br>
Remember -- without mages, alot of ubermobs wouldnt die.  We may not like it, but Trods are ESSENTIAL to quite a few fights out there.  I say we actually recognize that, be happy about it, but still note the places where our class ISNT balanced <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center></center>
